Sierra leone 
W. Coast of Africa
May 3rd 1877

To the Honorble
The secretary of state
Washington D.C.

Sir,

My health requiring a chance of climate I beg to inform you of my mention to go to maderi for about a four months 'stery.

During my absence same frame esqre the duty appointed Vice Consul further place, will take charge of this office, to do.

Trusting that you will approve of this temporary archive from Office.

I have the honor to be
Sir
You obedient servant
M Claudale 
U.S. Consul
